# Quick Sort

```python
def quick_sort(arr):

    if len(arr)<=1:
        return arr

    pivot=arr[len(arr)//2]

    left=[x for x in arr if x<pivot]

    middle=[x for x in arr if x==pivot]

    right=[x for x in arr if x>pivot]

    return quick_sort(left)+\
           middle+\
           quick_sort(right)

print(
quick_sort(
[5,2,8,1]
)
)
```

